      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 1178685
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-19T00:57:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do you mean lock in L68 and then unlock in L84?\nThat would prevent other threads from executing in parallel.\nNote that we don\u0027t need blameSize in L81 to have the same value as the blameSize in L68.\nA new blameSize could be set while this thread is running the query.",
      "parentUuid": "b31c35be_8b20bb1e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 82,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 82,
        "endChar": 15
